---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="FAQ | Macomb County Realty"
    description="Frequently asked questions about selling your house fast in Macomb County. We answer questions about cash offers, market listings, probate, foreclosure, and more."
>
    <main class="page-container">
        <section class="faq-page-header">
            <div class="faq-header-content">
                <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
                <p>Everything you need to know about selling your home with Macomb County Realty.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="faq-content-section">
            <div class="faq-category">
                <h2>📋 What Makes Macomb County Realty Different"</h2>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">Who is Macomb County Realty?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>We are a local, family-owned real estate solutions team led by the father-and-son duo of Max Mancini Sr. (Broker & Licensed Builder) and Max Mancini Jr. (Agent & Engineer). Our family has been proudly serving homeowners across Metro Detroit since 1994. Unlike national corporate call centers or out-of-state investment chains, you will work directly with us, 1-on-1, from your very first phone call to the day we close.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">How are you different from a traditional home buyer or a standard real estate agent?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Most real estate companies corner you into a single option. Direct investors only want to buy your house at a discount, while traditional agents only want to list it on the market.</p>
                        <p>We do both. Because we are both licensed real estate professionals and active local buyers, we provide you with a transparent, side-by-side comparison of what we can pay you in cash versus what your home could bring on the open market. You get total control to choose the path that best fits your financial goals and timeline.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">Am I under any obligation when I submit my info or ask for an offer?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Absolutely none. Requesting a consultation or a cash offer is 100% free and completely confidential. We review your property, explain your choices, and lay out the numbers. From there, it is entirely your decision. We give you the facts, and you tell us how you want to move forward.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-category">
                <div class="faq-path-header">
                    <h2>⚡ The Fast Track: All-Cash Offer FAQs</h2>
                    <p class="faq-path-desc">Best for speed, absolute certainty, and selling completely "as-is" without listing stress.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">Will you just make a "lowball" offer on my home?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>No. We calculate our cash offers transparently using real, recent neighborhood sales data and projected local renovation costs. While a direct cash offer is naturally below top retail market value, selling to us eliminates real estate agent commissions, staging costs, surprise repair bills, closing fees, and months of ongoing holding costs (like taxes, utilities, and insurance). When you run the numbers, you often net a very similar amount out-of-pocket, but with zero hassle.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">Are there any hidden fees, commissions, or surprise costs?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>None at all. The cash offer we give you is the exact amount of money you walk away with at closing. Because we buy the property directly from you, there are no agent commissions or marketing fees. Plus, we cover 100% of the standard closing costs.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">Do I need to clean up, paint, or make repairs first?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Not a single thing. We buy houses in absolute, 100% "as-is" condition. You don't need to pick up a paintbrush, hire a cleaning crew, or fix structural issues. You can even leave behind unwanted furniture, trash, or junk. Our team will handle the entire clean-out after the sale is finalized.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">How fast can we actually close on a cash sale?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>We can close in as little as 7 days, or we can schedule the closing date around your specific moving timeline. If you need a few weeks or even a month to get situated, we are completely flexible.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">What do you do with my house once you buy it?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>As licensed builders and local investors, we take on the risk of remodeling the property to bring it up to modern neighborhood standards. Once the home is fully renovated, we either sell it to a new family looking to move into the community or hold onto it as a local rental property.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-category">
                <div class="faq-path-header">
                    <h2>📈 The Retail Track: Open Market Listing FAQs</h2>
                    <p class="faq-path-desc">Best for homeowners who have time on their side and want to capture top-dollar market value.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">Why should I choose to list on the market instead of taking a quick cash offer?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>If your home is already updated, doesn't require massive structural repairs, and you aren't up against a strict timeline, listing on the open market is usually your best bet. It exposes your home to traditional retail buyers who buy with emotion. This maximum market exposure drives healthy competition, giving you the best opportunity to capture top dollar for your property.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">How do you determine the right listing price for my home?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>We conduct a deep-dive market analysis, evaluating recent sales of similar homes in your specific Michigan neighborhood, current competition, local buyer demand, and your property's unique features. From there, we recommend a targeted pricing strategy designed to attract qualified buyers and spark strong, competitive offers.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">How long does a traditional market listing take to close?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>While a cash sale wraps up in days, a traditional market listing typically takes between 30 to 60 days from the day it goes live to the final closing. This timeline accounts for scheduled showings, open houses, and the time it takes for a retail buyer's mortgage approval to clear.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">If I list with you, am I stuck paying high corporate commissions?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Not at all. If listing on the open market turns out to be the right move for you, Max will place your home on the MLS to capture the absolute highest price possible, while offering flexible, highly competitive commission structures to keep more equity in your pocket.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-category">
                <h2>🛠️ Handling Complex & Special Situations</h2>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">What if I inherited a house that is currently stuck in probate?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>We handle inherited properties and probate situations all the time across Macomb, Oakland, and Wayne counties. We can help you navigate the process cleanly. If the heirs want to split the proceeds quickly without pouring money into an inherited house that needs work, our cash offer is an excellent route. If the estate wants to maximize its value, we can list it.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">Can you help if I am falling behind on mortgage payments or facing foreclosure?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes, but timing is critical. Foreclosure is a stressful process, but you have options before the bank steps in completely. Because we can execute an all-cash close in as little as 7 days, we can frequently purchase the home quickly enough to pay off your lender, halt the foreclosure process, save your credit score, and potentially put cash back into your pocket.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">How do you handle property sales during a divorce?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Real estate decisions during a major life transition like a divorce are incredibly tough. We act as a neutral, professional third party. By providing a clear, transparent side-by-side breakdown of both a cash buyout and a market listing, we make sure both parties have the exact same data to make an informed, stress-free decision without the need for unnecessary friction or arguments.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section class="final-cta-section">
        <div class="cta-container">
            <h2 class="cta-heading cta-heading-about">
                Still have questions? 
            </h2>
            <p class="cta-subheading">
                We're here to help. Reach out to Max directly for a free, no-obligation consultation.
            </p>

            <div class="cta-actions">
                <a href="/contact" class="comparison-cta-btn"
                    >Get My Options ➔</a
                >

                <p class="cta-secondary-text final-cta-phone">
                    <strong>Call or Text:</strong><br />
                    <a href="tel:+15864157355" class="cta-phone-link"
                        >(586) 415–7355</a
                    >
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    </main>
</Layout>

<style>
    .page-container {
        padding: 4rem 1rem;
        max-width: 1000px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }
    
    .faq-page-header {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 4rem;
    }
    
    .faq-header-content h1 {
        font-size: 42px;
        font-weight: 800;
        color: #111111;
        line-height: 1.2;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    
    .faq-header-content p {
        font-size: 1.125rem;
        color: #4A6D7C;
        max-width: 600px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }
    
    .faq-content-section {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 3rem;
    }
    
    .faq-category > h2 {
        font-size: 1.75rem;
        color: #2E347A;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
        border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(46, 52, 122, 0.1);
    }
    
    .faq-path-header {
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
        border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(46, 52, 122, 0.1);
    }
    
    .faq-path-header h2 {
        font-size: 1.75rem;
        color: #2E347A;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    
    .faq-path-desc {
        color: #4A6D7C;
        font-style: italic;
    }
    
    .faq-item {
        background: #ffffff;
        border-radius: 18px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
        padding: 1rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
    }
    
    .faq-question {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        color: #000000;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        font-weight: 600;
    }
    
    .faq-answer p {
        color: #333333;
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    
    .faq-answer p:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }
    
    .faq-cta-section {
        margin-top: 5rem;
        text-align: center;
        background: #f8f9fa;
        padding: 3rem;
        border-radius: 12px;
    }
    
    .faq-cta-container h2 {
        color: #    2E347A;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    
    .faq-cta-container p {
        color: #4A6D7C;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    
    .faq-cta-buttons {
        display: flex;
        gap: 1rem;
        justify-content: center;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
    
    .btn-cta, .btn-secondary {
        padding: 0.75rem 2rem;
        border-radius: 4px;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: all 0.2s ease;
    }
    
    .btn-cta {
        background-color: #2E347A;
        color: white;
    }
    
    .btn-cta:hover {
        background-color: #1a1e4a;
    }
    
    .btn-secondary {
        background-color: transparent;
        color: #2E347A;
        border: 2px solid #2E347A;
    }
    
    .btn-secondary:hover {
        background-color: #2E347A;
        color: white;
    }
    
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .faq-header-content h1 {
            font-size: 2rem;
        }
        
        .faq-item {
            padding: 1.25rem;
        }
    }
</style>
